      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DENIS THE PUNTER (2) resumes from a spell of 22 months after closing off last campaign in good form, the last run being a solid third over 1850m at this track. No excuses from this advantageous draw. Will have plenty of admirers. BETTOR BE BODHI (5) finished fourth last start, beaten 10 metres at Redcliffe over 1780m. Capable of playing a major role so has to be respected. VICE CHAIRWOMAN NZ (3) broke last start and finished a distant seventh over 1850m at this track when resuming. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Meets a similar line up so if she behaves a big run is likely. TORI TIME (1) is a three-year-old filly from the Gemma Hewitt stable on debut. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Showed some ability when a minor placegetter in a recent trial. Makes plenty of appeal.",
